## Introduction

This document aims to collect some useful resources for learning about [Free and Open Source Software](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open-source_software).

## Links

1. [The Freenode's ##programming chatroom’s Frequently Asked Questions](https://github.com/shlomif/Freenode-programming-channel-FAQ/blob/master/FAQ.mdwn)
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open-source_software
2. [The Haifa Linux Club’s Lectures](http://haifux.org/)

3. [The Tel Aviv Open Source Club’s Lectures](http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/telux/advanced.html)

4. [The Awesome Books Lists on GitHub](https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome#books) - includes [a list of free programming books](https://github.com/EbookFoundation/free-programming-books).

5. [“How to start contributing to or using Open Source Software”](http://old.teachingopensource.org/index.php/How_to_start_contributing_to_or_using_Open_Source_Software)

6. [The Linux Documentation Project](http://tldp.org/) - somewhat outdated, but may prove of enlightenment. Especially see [this](http://tldp.org/HOWTO/Unix-and-Internet-Fundamentals-HOWTO/).

